<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-794-940  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 794 940.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  August 27 1990 v7 n35 p4(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI says it will accelerate net digitization by 2 years. (MCICommunications Corp.'s network development plans)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wallace, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp will expand and upgrade its networkbetween 1990 and 1992, speeding up its previous timeframe fordigitizing the network in order to compete against AT and T and USSprint Communications Co, both of which have more fiber routesmiles than MCI.andP;  Digitization will reportedly be completed by theend of 1991.andP;  To fund the effort, the company may use a $500 to$550 million write-down to retire its analog equipment, which ismore costly to maintain than digital equipment.andP;  MCI also plans toassimilate 3,000 fiber miles it gained from a merger withTelecom*USA, and the company will gain access to WilliamsTelecommunications Group Inc's digital links.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (planning)Williams Telecommunications Group Inc. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     Long-Distance Telephone ServicesDigital CommunicationsBusiness PlanningFiber OpticsUpgradingExpansion.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>